	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-08-20T07:35:35">DRS Data and Research Services plc is a United Kingdom-based holding company. The Company is a provider of automated data capture technology and solutions in the United Kingdom and overseas to three market sectors: education, elections and census. The Company is engaged in the provision of software, data capture services, the manufacture, sale and support of optical and image scanning equipment, design and printing of documentation used for data capture and bureau services. The Company provides an end-to-end solution for electronically counted elections, including form design and printing, hardware, software, project support and training. The Company's census services provide data capture solutions for censuses, including paper-based national or regional population censuses and specialized industrial, commercial and agricultural censuses. The Company's subsidiary includes DRS Data Services Limited.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-10-31T11:41:06">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, DRS Data &amp; Research Services plc revenues decreased 34% to L3.6M. Net loss decreased 31% to L1.8M. Revenues reflect Examination and assesment segment decrease of 25% to L3.2M, Census &amp; elections segment decrease of 87% to L90K, Africa segment decrease of 45% to L1M, Rest of the World segment decrease of 75% to L185K. Lower net loss reflects Selling and marketing costs decrease of 48% to L346K (expense).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
